column15: x # basically just translated the English titles

column2: The Tapado is selected in secret by the Emperador and then revealed publicly with "el Dedazo"  the finger  to be his chosen successor upon his death. Only very rarely does the transition of power not follow the traditions of el Dedazo.
The title of Presidente was once one of the many great titles given to the Emperador. Now it is a ceremonial position granted to his children or relatives
The Grand Corridero must chronicle the heroic deeds of the Emperador in the form of song so that he will be remembered for generations to come.
The Commandant of the Academy is in charge of the Heroic Military College that is responsible for producing the next generation of leaders for the Empire.
The Majordomo of Feasts is responsible for making sure all of the holy days and feast days are given proper celebrations.
The Compadre of the ruler is their closest friend. He helps the ruler in all aspects of life and especially with the raising of his children.
The Grand Muralist is responsible for the commissioning and patronage of murals  works of art that span the great walls of the cities of the Empire and recount its glory to the illiterate peasantry.
